"title": "8325: purity, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8325",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The OT recognises a close link between outer cleanliness and inner purity. In the NT, special emphasis is placed on inner purity resulting from spiritual renewal.</p>\n<h2>Physical cleansing from impurity by washing or refining</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:4\">GEN 18:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:30\">JOB 9:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:6\">PSA 12:6</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual impurity must be avoided or cleansed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:10-Lev10:11\">LEV 10:10–10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:8\">ISA 35:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:1\">ISA 52:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:2\">MRK 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:4\">MRK 7:4</a></p>\n<h2>Sexual sources of ritual impurity</h2>\n<h3>Childbirth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:2\">LEV 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:5\">LEV 12:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22\">LUK 2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual intercourse</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:15\">EXO 19:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:18\">LEV 15:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4\">1SA 21:4</a></p>\n<h3>Seminal emission</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:16-Lev15:17\">LEV 15:16–15:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:10-Deut23:11\">DEU 23:10–23:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:26\">1SA 20:26</a></p>\n<h3>Menstruation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:19-Lev15:20\">LEV 15:19–15:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:2–11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:6\">EZK 18:6</a></p>\n<h3>Abnormal discharge</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:1-Lev15:2\">LEV 15:1–15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:25-Lev15:27\">LEV 15:25–15:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:20\">MAT 9:20</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25\">MRK 5:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:43\">LUK 8:43</a></p>\n<h2>Other sources of ritual impurity</h2>\n<h3>Dead bodies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11-Num19:16\">NUM 19:11–19:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Unclean creatures</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:2\">GEN 7:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:24\">LEV 11:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:46-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:46–11:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:3\">DEU 14:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:3\">HOS 9:3</a></p>\n<h3>Skin diseases</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:45\">LEV 13:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:2-Matt8:4\">MAT 8:2–8:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:44\">MRK 1:40–1:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:14\">LUK 5:12–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Mildew</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:36\">LEV 14:36</a></p>\n<h3>Contact with a sin offering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:26\">LEV 16:26</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Cleansing from ritual impurity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:8\">LEV 14:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:26\">LEV 16:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:17-Num19:21\">NUM 19:17–19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:9\">NUM 19:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:17-Num19:21\">NUM 19:17–19:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:22-Num31:23\">NUM 31:22–31:23</a> <em>Fire is also a purifying agent.</em></p>\n<h2>Contact with God demanded purity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:10\">EXO 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:14-Exod19:15\">EXO 19:14–19:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:18-Exod30:21\">EXO 30:18–30:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual purity is not required under the new covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:11\">MAT 15:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:15\">MRK 7:15</a> <em>What concerns God is moral impurity, associated with actions, not ritual impurity, associated with food, etc.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:12-Acts10:15\">ACT 10:12–10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:26\">ACT 21:26</a> <em>Paul took part in Jewish purification rites in accordance with his Jewish heritage</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:14\">ROM 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:11-Gal2:12\">GAL 2:11–2:12</a> <em>Peter temporarily relapsed into the habit of treating Gentiles as unclean</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:14-Gal2:15\">GAL 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:4\">1TI 4:4</a></p>",
